{"key":"post-17997128","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>17997128</id>\n<content>Oven drying can ruin them.&amp;nbsp; When using a dehydrator they dry much faster and the actives seem to be preserved better.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Yes, I've grilled them too.&amp;nbsp; Prepared properly, cubensis is a gourmet edible.&amp;nbsp; Some of the actives are destroyed by the grill but that's a good thing when eating a meal. &lt;img style=&quot;max-width:192px;height:auto;&quot; src=&quot;https://files.shroomery.org/smileys/wink.gif&quot; alt=&quot;:wink:&quot; title=&quot;:wink:&quot;/&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You can boil them in water to make tea with very little degradation, but that same temperature in dry heat nukes them pretty bad.&amp;nbsp; It's best to fan dry only, and then use desiccant.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>17997364</next>\n<prev>17997075</prev>\n<first>17996027</first>\n<last>18002247</last>\n<when>1364012039</when>\n<utime>03/23/13 07:13 AM</utime>\n</post>"}